		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64339607"><p>Reducing solar input reduces heat... which allows us to ignore increasing CO2 and ocean acidity.  We will not use it as a respite to reduce atmospheric CO2, we'll use it as an excuse to continue making the underlying problem worse (at a faster rate, we're already continuing to make it worse).</p><p>Given the scale of such projects, we're also slaving ourselves to a massive maintenance budget (<i>forever</i>) that you know is going to get slashed as soon as someone doesn't feel like carrying the expense.</p><p>There are only two things we should be targeting right now - constantly and consistently working towards a carbon-neutral economy, and using any and all excess energy whenever and wherever to remove CO2 from the atmosphere and permanently sequester it until we're back to 1800s levels.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64339607">
